00:05:16.480 --> 00:05:19.930
So the word Veda itself
comes from the Sanskrit

00:05:19.930 --> 00:05:24.640
root [INAUDIBLE],
which means "to know."

00:05:24.640 --> 00:05:28.680
We know our environment
through various means.

00:05:28.680 --> 00:05:30.500
Through the five
senses-- seeing,

00:05:30.500 --> 00:05:33.570
hearing, touching,
feeling, tasting.

00:05:33.570 --> 00:05:38.220
There's so much input that
happens to this nervous system.

00:05:38.220 --> 00:05:40.880
All of the methods of knowing
all the ways in which we

00:05:40.880 --> 00:05:42.700
are knowing gets put together.

00:05:42.700 --> 00:05:44.510
All the knowledge
that we accumulate

00:05:44.510 --> 00:05:48.810
comes together as the Veda.

00:05:48.810 --> 00:05:53.710
As more and more scientists
add to this body of knowledge,

00:05:53.710 --> 00:05:55.510
it grows vaster and vaster.

00:05:58.270 --> 00:06:01.200
Initially, when they
started printing books,

00:06:01.200 --> 00:06:03.410
books were a very
rare commodity.

00:06:03.410 --> 00:06:05.710
And then they started
getting stored in places.

00:06:08.800 --> 00:06:12.260
Very soon, there
were so many books

00:06:12.260 --> 00:06:15.110
that there was a need
to categorize them.

00:06:15.110 --> 00:06:17.380
And the library system
came into existence.

00:06:20.690 --> 00:06:22.710
I don't know if people
still remember--

00:06:22.710 --> 00:06:27.310
there's the Dewey Decimal
system of numbering books based

00:06:27.310 --> 00:06:30.380
on the topic.

00:06:30.380 --> 00:06:33.550
So as the subjects
got vaster, they

00:06:33.550 --> 00:06:37.500
started cataloguing
them and arranging them.

00:06:37.500 --> 00:06:40.050
That's what happened
in ancient India, too.

00:06:40.050 --> 00:06:42.850
And they called it "The Vedas."

00:06:42.850 --> 00:06:48.360
They said, based on the kind of
knowledge, let's categorize it.

00:06:48.360 --> 00:06:49.860
So the first thing
they did was they

00:06:49.860 --> 00:06:52.230
said, OK, there are four Vedas.

00:06:52.230 --> 00:06:55.200
Let's categorize
all this knowledge

00:06:55.200 --> 00:06:57.720
and put it into four buckets.

00:06:57.720 --> 00:07:01.170
So the first bucket was
called the the "Rigveda."

00:07:01.170 --> 00:07:12.264
The Rigveda is all about
the principles, or the,

00:07:12.264 --> 00:07:14.610
for want of a better
word, principles.

00:07:17.940 --> 00:07:21.730
Then comes the Yajurveda,
which means the application

00:07:21.730 --> 00:07:23.960
of those principles.

00:07:23.960 --> 00:07:27.030
Then comes the
Samaveda, which has

00:07:27.030 --> 00:07:30.100
to do with the rhythm,
or the harmony,

00:07:30.100 --> 00:07:33.790
or the beauty, the music.

00:07:33.790 --> 00:07:35.460
And then comes the
Atharvaveda, which

00:07:35.460 --> 00:07:39.960
is about our mundane existence,
about our day to day lives.

00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:41.690
So if you look at
knowledge, there

00:07:41.690 --> 00:07:46.340
are different
types of-- e equals

00:07:46.340 --> 00:07:48.350
mc squared was an equation.

00:07:48.350 --> 00:07:51.750
There are so many equations
that we learn in college

00:07:51.750 --> 00:07:55.690
but hardly ever use later on.

00:07:55.690 --> 00:07:59.530
Maybe we all had to go through
differentiation and integration

00:07:59.530 --> 00:08:02.100
calculus.

00:08:02.100 --> 00:08:05.380
And after the exam was
over, very few people

00:08:05.380 --> 00:08:06.120
actually use it.

00:08:06.120 --> 00:08:07.440
Maybe you actually use it here.

00:08:07.440 --> 00:08:10.090
I have no idea.

00:08:10.090 --> 00:08:13.370
But if you look at it, there
are a lot of principles,

00:08:13.370 --> 00:08:15.815
and then there are application
of those principles.

00:08:19.410 --> 00:08:23.920
Some people are more interested
in ideation, in ideas.

00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:26.346
And some people are more
interested in application

00:08:26.346 --> 00:08:26.970
of those ideas.

00:08:29.620 --> 00:08:35.539
So those who are
more ideation, more

00:08:35.539 --> 00:08:40.870
getting to the basic principles,
I would say they are Rigvedis.

00:08:40.870 --> 00:08:45.260
Their brain makeup is more
of the kind of Rigveda.

00:08:45.260 --> 00:08:47.560
And if you put them to
do something practical,

00:08:47.560 --> 00:08:48.400
it doesn't work.

00:08:51.660 --> 00:08:55.610
There are some people who
love to make things practical.

00:08:55.610 --> 00:09:00.740
Bring it down to existence.

00:09:00.740 --> 00:09:04.000
For example, if
you take a string,

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:06.890
stretch it and
pluck it, it's going

00:09:06.890 --> 00:09:09.650
to vibrate at a
certain frequency.

00:09:09.650 --> 00:09:12.490
If you change the length
of the string, the tension

00:09:12.490 --> 00:09:15.130
of the string, the
material of the string,

00:09:15.130 --> 00:09:18.540
it's going to change the
frequency at which it vibrates.

00:09:18.540 --> 00:09:22.040
That's Rigveda, the principle.

00:09:22.040 --> 00:09:24.420
Someone said, OK,
this is the principle.

00:09:24.420 --> 00:09:27.960
Let's put six strings
on a piece of wood,

00:09:27.960 --> 00:09:31.140
put some frets and we
make it into a guitar.

00:09:31.140 --> 00:09:33.930
It's the same principle,
but it's now come down

00:09:33.930 --> 00:09:36.810
into the form of a guitar.

00:09:36.810 --> 00:09:39.000
That's Yajurveda.

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:42.030
A person who does the
research on the stress

00:09:42.030 --> 00:09:45.420
and tension in the string has
nothing to do with the guitar.

00:09:45.420 --> 00:09:47.440
And a person who
makes the guitar,

00:09:47.440 --> 00:09:49.050
he just needs to
know the equations.

00:09:49.050 --> 00:09:52.150
He's not worried
about how it works.

00:09:52.150 --> 00:09:55.410
If I have a phone,
most probably I

00:09:55.410 --> 00:09:57.250
would look at the
features inside it.

00:09:57.250 --> 00:09:59.240
A person who's
designing the phone

00:09:59.240 --> 00:10:02.231
would probably look at all the
processes that go behind it.

00:10:06.950 --> 00:10:11.570
You give me a guitar, I
can probably make sound.

00:10:11.570 --> 00:10:16.070
But if I have to create music,
I need to know how to play it.

00:10:16.070 --> 00:10:18.830
So even if you have
something very practical,

00:10:18.830 --> 00:10:22.200
unless we know how
to create music,

00:10:22.200 --> 00:10:24.020
that's another level of knowing.

00:10:26.570 --> 00:10:29.350
I can appreciate good
music, but to create

00:10:29.350 --> 00:10:31.340
that music needs another skill.

00:10:31.340 --> 00:10:35.770
And that skill is the
Samaveda, how to create music.

00:10:35.770 --> 00:10:37.130
How to create harmony.

00:10:37.130 --> 00:10:40.000
When I say music, it
doesn't mean just music,

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:43.460
but how to use that practical
knowledge and create harmony,

00:10:43.460 --> 00:10:44.340
make it beautiful.

00:10:48.190 --> 00:10:53.010
Different types of music
affect us in different ways.

00:10:53.010 --> 00:10:55.030
If someone plays some
tune, you probably

00:10:55.030 --> 00:10:57.380
want to stand up and dance.

00:10:57.380 --> 00:11:00.070
Some other music makes
you feel, OK, I just

00:11:00.070 --> 00:11:03.190
want to close my eyes and relax.

00:11:03.190 --> 00:11:08.290
Impact of that knowledge
on the human psyche,

00:11:08.290 --> 00:11:11.430
that's a different
ball game altogether.

00:11:11.430 --> 00:11:13.500
There are people who
make great music,

00:11:13.500 --> 00:11:15.710
and there are people who
can analyze that music.

00:11:18.630 --> 00:11:21.260
So in this example,
if you look at it,

00:11:21.260 --> 00:11:26.430
the equations of the stretched
string, that's Rigveda.

00:11:26.430 --> 00:11:30.930
Creating the guitar
was the Yajurveda.

00:11:30.930 --> 00:11:34.330
The Samaveda is how to
make music out of it.

00:11:34.330 --> 00:11:36.490
And what impact
does that music have

00:11:36.490 --> 00:11:39.238
on people, groups of people,
that's the [INAUDIBLE].

00:11:42.590 --> 00:11:46.600
Each of us usually has one or
a couple of these capabilities.

00:11:46.600 --> 00:11:51.150
Some of us are great at ideas,
not good at implementing.

00:11:51.150 --> 00:11:55.480
Some of us are great
managers, but not very

00:11:55.480 --> 00:11:58.450
good at creating harmony.

00:11:58.450 --> 00:12:01.350
Some people can get
groups of people together,

00:12:01.350 --> 00:12:03.240
make it all work.

00:12:03.240 --> 00:12:07.250
But if you have to do something
practical, it doesn't work.

00:12:07.250 --> 00:12:12.940
And some people are at the
front and can look at the impact

00:12:12.940 --> 00:12:15.130
that this is going
to have on people

00:12:15.130 --> 00:12:17.880
and make decisions
according to that.

00:12:17.880 --> 00:12:20.910
So if we look at all these
four aspects of knowing,

00:12:20.910 --> 00:12:24.450
it translates to how
we live our life.

00:12:24.450 --> 00:12:27.200
Sometimes, we have one
of these Vedas in excess.

00:12:27.200 --> 00:12:28.790
Others, we don't have.

00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:31.630
And we wonder, why
am I not progressing?

00:12:31.630 --> 00:12:35.100
What is it that I
need to focus on?

00:12:35.100 --> 00:12:39.790
So if you look at these four
Vedas, then it gives us a clue.

00:12:39.790 --> 00:12:41.900
Where can I put some attention?

00:12:41.900 --> 00:12:44.650
Where do I need to move ahead?

00:12:44.650 --> 00:12:49.410
Maybe you're great at
harmonizing with people,

00:12:49.410 --> 00:12:53.500
but ideation might
not be so good.

00:12:53.500 --> 00:12:56.360
So there are two
things we can do.

00:12:56.360 --> 00:12:59.100
They said if you have
to learn these Vedas,

00:12:59.100 --> 00:13:01.810
if you have to become
proficient in the Vedas,

00:13:01.810 --> 00:13:03.630
they said there
are six Vedangas.

00:13:03.630 --> 00:13:06.267
There are six
aspects to this Veda.

00:13:10.650 --> 00:13:15.200
The six limbs of the Veda.

00:13:15.200 --> 00:13:16.970
Anga means "limb."

00:13:16.970 --> 00:13:19.690
For example, if I have
a body, but the hands

00:13:19.690 --> 00:13:22.790
enable me to do
something with them.

00:13:22.790 --> 00:13:25.790
I might have a great
idea, but to type it out,

00:13:25.790 --> 00:13:28.280
I need my fingers.

00:13:28.280 --> 00:13:32.490
I use my legs to take my body
from one place to another.

00:13:32.490 --> 00:13:38.010
So in that sense, the limbs help
the body to function properly.

00:13:38.010 --> 00:13:40.000
And this is what
the Vedangas do.

00:13:43.020 --> 00:13:46.830
The Angas starts with Shiksha.

00:13:46.830 --> 00:13:49.330
Shiksha means how
to create the sound.

00:13:53.420 --> 00:13:56.800
When I say something when
I'm speaking something,

00:13:56.800 --> 00:13:58.990
I'm creating sound.

00:13:58.990 --> 00:14:01.310
And if I need to
communicate properly,

00:14:01.310 --> 00:14:03.610
if I need to
understand properly,

00:14:03.610 --> 00:14:09.630
first I need to go into the
root of-- so creating the sound.

00:14:09.630 --> 00:14:12.920
Then comes Nirukta,
or how to put

00:14:12.920 --> 00:14:14.905
sounds together to create words.

00:14:18.440 --> 00:14:21.810
Then comes Vyakarana, or
how do I put words together

00:14:21.810 --> 00:14:22.830
to create sentences.

00:14:26.020 --> 00:14:29.520
Then comes Chandas, what is
the rhythm in the sentence.

00:14:29.520 --> 00:14:34.260
The same sentence, when
I speak in a certain way,

00:14:34.260 --> 00:14:36.320
creates a certain impact.

00:14:36.320 --> 00:14:38.936
Spoken in another way, it
creates another impact.

