So [INAUDIBLE] said,
the Vedic scholar

00:17:28.300 --> 00:17:33.100
said, let's address all
these mindsets separately.

00:17:33.100 --> 00:17:36.350
So the first one is
called Nyaya, or logic.

00:17:36.350 --> 00:17:37.940
There are some people
who are logical,

00:17:37.940 --> 00:17:41.880
who need a reason
for everything.

00:17:41.880 --> 00:17:47.220
Someone comes and says, oh,
this meditation is excellent.

00:17:47.220 --> 00:17:49.534
And the question
is, OK, who says so?

00:17:49.534 --> 00:17:50.450
Where is the research?

00:17:54.250 --> 00:17:55.530
Where are the testimonials?

00:17:55.530 --> 00:17:56.810
I want proof.

00:17:56.810 --> 00:18:00.270
So some of our minds work
proof and logic, Nyaya.

00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:06.100
There is conversely
another attitude

00:18:06.100 --> 00:18:09.330
which says it doesn't matter
what everyone is saying,

00:18:09.330 --> 00:18:11.390
I want to know for myself.

00:18:11.390 --> 00:18:14.720
