00:18:14.720 --> 00:18:16.720
That is Vaisheshika, vaishesha.

00:18:16.720 --> 00:18:20.980
"Vaishesha" means
"special" or "knowing."

00:18:20.980 --> 00:18:23.810
So the first darshana
is Nyaya, or logic.

00:18:23.810 --> 00:18:28.890
And the second is Vaisheshika,
or personal experience.

00:18:28.890 --> 00:18:31.200
Now if you look at
people around you,

00:18:31.200 --> 00:18:33.720
there are some people
who need logic,

00:18:33.720 --> 00:18:36.890
some people who need
to have testimonials,

00:18:36.890 --> 00:18:38.250
who need to have proof.

00:18:38.250 --> 00:18:40.220
And there are some people
who base their life

00:18:40.220 --> 00:18:41.907
on experience-- I want to know.

00:18:44.770 --> 00:18:49.240
If you talk to a Nyaya person
in a Vaisheshika manner,

00:18:49.240 --> 00:18:51.050
a person who likes
logic and you tell them,

00:18:51.050 --> 00:18:53.050
no, no, you sit
here and experience.

00:18:53.050 --> 00:18:56.560
He says, no, I'm not interested.

00:18:56.560 --> 00:19:01.860
And if a person is interested
in Vaisheshika, in experience,

00:19:01.860 --> 00:19:06.244
and you throw numbers and facts
and figures at them, they say,

00:19:06.244 --> 00:19:07.410
all this doesn't impress me.

00:19:07.410 --> 00:19:13.910
Show me the result.
Nyaya and Vaisheshika.

