Keep pulling the fingers
towards yourself.

00:31:38.830 --> 00:31:40.780
Push away with the
palm, as if you're

00:31:40.780 --> 00:31:41.965
trying to push the walls.

00:31:45.520 --> 00:31:48.055
If you look at me so seriously,
I feel really afraid.

00:31:51.640 --> 00:31:53.110
And release.

00:31:53.110 --> 00:31:55.990
Bring the hands down.

00:31:55.990 --> 00:31:59.020
Interlock the hands together,
the fingers together,

00:31:59.020 --> 00:32:00.810
and place them behind the head.

00:32:05.010 --> 00:32:08.450
Gently press the head
forward with the hands.

00:32:08.450 --> 00:32:11.420
Push the head forward
with the hands.

00:32:11.420 --> 00:32:13.600
With your head,
push the hands back.

00:32:13.600 --> 00:32:14.460
Nothing is moving.

00:32:14.460 --> 00:32:15.835
You're just feeling
the pressure.

00:32:19.230 --> 00:32:23.740
And as you breathe in, push
the elbows back a little bit.

00:32:23.740 --> 00:32:25.045
Stay there and keep breathing.

00:32:29.270 --> 00:32:31.370
And gently release the hands.

00:32:31.370 --> 00:32:32.110
Bring them down.

00:32:35.490 --> 00:32:37.950
With the right hand,
press the right side

00:32:37.950 --> 00:32:44.000
of the head-- with your
right hand, or some hand.

00:32:44.000 --> 00:32:47.210
And gently press the head.

00:32:47.210 --> 00:32:49.240
With your neck, you're
resisting that pressure.

00:32:54.790 --> 00:32:58.350
It's OK to smile.

00:32:58.350 --> 00:33:00.370
And gently release the hand.

00:33:00.370 --> 00:33:02.934
Other side.

00:33:02.934 --> 00:33:04.250
A gentle pressure.

00:33:09.150 --> 00:33:14.060
Feeling the sensation on
the neck, in the upper back.

00:33:14.060 --> 00:33:15.740
And gently release the hands.

00:33:19.030 --> 00:33:21.169
Once again, let's
roll our shoulders.

00:33:21.169 --> 00:33:22.085
Notice the difference.

00:33:25.110 --> 00:33:26.815
And in the opposite direction.

00:33:33.180 --> 00:33:34.135
And relax.

00:33:37.040 --> 00:33:39.695
Gently bring the ears
towards the shoulders.

00:33:44.330 --> 00:33:48.080
If you feel some discomfort,
do not go too much.

00:33:48.080 --> 00:33:49.590
Just do as much as you can.

00:33:52.480 --> 00:33:55.010
Keeping the neck straight,
look left and right.

00:33:59.500 --> 00:34:03.181
If you want to lose weight,
this is the perfect pose to do.

00:34:05.752 --> 00:34:07.710
Just do this when there's
food in front of you.

00:34:12.060 --> 00:34:12.960
And relax.

00:34:19.580 --> 00:34:22.480
Interlock the hands
in front of the chest.

00:34:22.480 --> 00:34:24.520
And this time,
twist a little bit.

00:34:24.520 --> 00:34:27.090
Breathing out,
twist to the side.

00:34:27.090 --> 00:34:29.010
Breathe in to center.

00:34:29.010 --> 00:34:31.780
Breathe out, twist to the side.

00:34:31.780 --> 00:34:34.230
Breathe in to center.

00:34:34.230 --> 00:34:39.650
Breathe out to the side,
breathe in to center.

00:34:39.650 --> 00:34:43.199
Breathe out to the
side, breathe in center

00:34:43.199 --> 00:34:45.139
and come back to center, relax.

00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:52.860
Place the hands on the
knees in front of you.

00:34:56.420 --> 00:34:57.980
As you breathe in, look up.

00:34:57.980 --> 00:35:01.000
Push the chest forward.

00:35:01.000 --> 00:35:04.420
And as we exhale, let's
bring the chin to the chest,

00:35:04.420 --> 00:35:07.630
arch the back behind us.

00:35:07.630 --> 00:35:09.800
Breathing in, look up.

00:35:09.800 --> 00:35:12.420
Push the chest forward.

00:35:12.420 --> 00:35:14.300
Exhale, arch the back.

00:35:14.300 --> 00:35:16.890
Bring the chin to the chest.

00:35:16.890 --> 00:35:17.610
Once again.

00:35:17.610 --> 00:35:21.310
Breathe in, look up.

00:35:21.310 --> 00:35:26.440
Exhale, arch the back,
bring the chin to the chest.

00:35:26.440 --> 00:35:27.430
And relax.

00:35:32.830 --> 00:35:37.220
Gently, as we breathe out,
let the shoulders move

00:35:37.220 --> 00:35:39.250
to the right.

00:35:39.250 --> 00:35:41.490
Breathe in to center.

00:35:41.490 --> 00:35:44.780
Breathe out, bend a
little bit to the left.

00:35:44.780 --> 00:35:47.560
Breathe in to center.

00:35:47.560 --> 00:35:50.530
Breathe out to the right.

00:35:50.530 --> 00:35:52.950
Breathe in, center.

00:35:52.950 --> 00:35:55.390
Breathe out, left.

00:35:55.390 --> 00:35:56.520
Breathe in, center.

00:35:56.520 --> 00:35:57.280
And relax.

00:36:00.220 --> 00:36:04.050
The three major movements for
our spine-- front and back,

00:36:04.050 --> 00:36:06.690
twisting, and sideways.

00:36:06.690 --> 00:36:11.180
If you can just do
these few things,

00:36:11.180 --> 00:36:15.520
it helps to keep the spine
held in a certain way.

00:36:15.520 --> 00:36:17.910
A lot of times,
sitting in one posture,

00:36:17.910 --> 00:36:21.320
we do not do these movements.

00:36:21.320 --> 00:36:24.640
So just a few of
these movements can

00:36:24.640 --> 00:36:31.050
help to relax a lot of the
muscle systems of the spine.

00:36:31.050 --> 00:36:34.270
And once the body is relaxed,
then it's easier to meditate.

00:36:34.270 --> 00:36:37.000
Otherwise what happens
when we start to meditate,

00:36:37.000 --> 00:36:38.990
then suddenly we
realize we have a body.

00:36:41.920 --> 00:36:46.700
If you're sitting for watching
a movie, three hours, two hours,

00:36:46.700 --> 00:36:49.010
you can sit perfectly still.

00:36:49.010 --> 00:36:51.770
But when you sit for
meditation, in five minutes,

00:36:51.770 --> 00:36:53.250
you say, oh, I have back pain.

00:36:56.150 --> 00:36:59.330
Which is why doing some gentle
movements like this, very

00:36:59.330 --> 00:37:02.700
useful before a meditation.

00:37:02.700 --> 00:37:05.719
Then we'll go on to a
breathing technique.

00:37:05.719 --> 00:37:07.760
Now this is called,
variously, nadi [? sodhana ?]

00:37:07.760 --> 00:37:13.680
and [? anuloma viloma, ?] or
alternate nostril breathing.

00:37:13.680 --> 00:37:15.700
Many ways in which to do it.

00:37:18.340 --> 00:37:22.140
But what this-- the way
we'll be doing it here

00:37:22.140 --> 00:37:28.070
today, our whole purpose is to
breathe in from one nostril,

00:37:28.070 --> 00:37:29.450
breathe out from the other.

00:37:29.450 --> 00:37:31.783
Breathe in from one nostril,
breathe out from the other.

00:37:34.240 --> 00:37:34.880
Don't worry.

00:37:34.880 --> 00:37:35.860
We'll have some help.

00:37:35.860 --> 00:37:39.710
If you think only
superhumans can do that,

00:37:39.710 --> 00:37:43.500
I don't think I can-- like.

00:37:43.500 --> 00:37:46.400
So we're going to
use our fingers.

00:37:46.400 --> 00:37:50.650
Place our hands
in this position.

00:37:50.650 --> 00:37:57.730
It's like the thumb on the
right nostril, index finger

00:37:57.730 --> 00:38:02.650
and middle finger in between
the eyebrows, and ring finger

00:38:02.650 --> 00:38:05.760
and little finger, you can
bend them and place them

00:38:05.760 --> 00:38:08.930
on the left nostril.

00:38:08.930 --> 00:38:13.330
So this is the position
for the fingers.

00:38:13.330 --> 00:38:17.860
Now, the middle two
fingers-- the index finger

00:38:17.860 --> 00:38:21.040
and the middle finger--
gently touching

00:38:21.040 --> 00:38:22.720
in between the eyebrows.

00:38:22.720 --> 00:38:27.050
So | want, in this technique,
all the five fingers

00:38:27.050 --> 00:38:29.630
to touch the skin.

00:38:29.630 --> 00:38:33.470
And we'll move as
little as possible.

00:38:33.470 --> 00:38:38.200
So what we're going to do is
either increase the pressure

00:38:38.200 --> 00:38:41.780
from the thumb or increase the
pressure with the ring finger.

00:38:41.780 --> 00:38:43.930
Without moving the
hands, it's just

00:38:43.930 --> 00:38:48.830
going to change the pressure
and control the breath flow,

00:38:48.830 --> 00:38:52.550
moving it either right or left.

00:38:52.550 --> 00:38:56.800
So let's keep our
hands in this position.

00:38:56.800 --> 00:38:59.440
With the eyes closed, breathe
in from both nostrils.

00:39:02.386 --> 00:39:04.975
Press the thumb, exhale left.

00:39:08.860 --> 00:39:15.370
Breathe in left,
and exhale right.

00:39:18.840 --> 00:39:24.380
Breathe in right,
and exhale left.

00:39:28.440 --> 00:39:30.520
Breathe in left.

00:39:30.520 --> 00:39:32.320
Continue at your own pace.

00:39:32.320 --> 00:39:37.120
Gentle breaths, moving the
hands as little as possible.

00:39:57.190 --> 00:40:00.639
Four more breaths
in this fashion.

00:40:00.639 --> 00:40:02.180
Put all your attention
on the breath.

00:40:16.850 --> 00:40:19.070
And after breathing
out from the left side,

00:40:19.070 --> 00:40:21.495
we may relax the hands,
keep the eyes closed.

00:40:34.120 --> 00:40:36.670
Keeping the eyes closed,
let's bring our hands

00:40:36.670 --> 00:40:38.875
onto the laps, palms
facing upwards.

00:40:50.500 --> 00:40:53.722
Gently, let's take
a deep breath in.

00:40:56.890 --> 00:40:58.035
And gently, exhale.

00:41:07.060 --> 00:41:10.340
Let's take the attention to
all the sounds around us,

00:41:10.340 --> 00:41:11.540
keeping the eyes closed.

00:41:17.480 --> 00:41:22.016
The sounds of people walking
behind or talking, gentle

00:41:22.016 --> 00:41:22.515
sounds.

00:41:33.070 --> 00:41:34.620
Breathing in once again.

00:41:37.720 --> 00:41:39.770
And gently, let's breathe out.

00:42:01.110 --> 00:42:04.385
Allow the breath to go
in and out all by itself.

00:42:07.000 --> 00:42:09.480
Without changing the
flow of the breathe,

00:42:09.480 --> 00:42:13.350
just observe how the
breath is flowing.

00:42:13.350 --> 00:42:19.460
It might be long or
short, shallow or deep.

00:42:23.650 --> 00:42:26.216
Let there be a gentle
smile on the face,

00:42:26.216 --> 00:42:27.215
even if it's artificial.

00:42:30.850 --> 00:42:32.100
With a smile, breathe in.

00:42:35.420 --> 00:42:36.740
And breathe out with a smile.

00:43:00.590 --> 00:43:03.150
For a few minutes,
for a few seconds,

00:43:03.150 --> 00:43:05.960
let's keep our body
as still as possible.

00:43:08.470 --> 00:43:09.550
The feet are still.

00:43:09.550 --> 00:43:13.490
The legs, knees, and thighs.

00:43:19.210 --> 00:43:21.020
The spine is still and erect.

00:43:25.950 --> 00:43:29.440
As the breath moves
in and out, there's

00:43:29.440 --> 00:43:32.350
a rhythmic motion
happening all by itself.

00:43:35.400 --> 00:43:37.230
The hands are still.

00:43:37.230 --> 00:43:38.100
The neck is still.

00:43:41.016 --> 00:43:44.680
And let the whole body
be as still as possible.

00:43:56.100 --> 00:43:59.560
You might experience
a little discomfort.

00:43:59.560 --> 00:44:02.528
Just for the next few
seconds, let's be with that.

00:44:29.430 --> 00:44:31.820
For a little while,
nothing to do.

00:44:31.820 --> 00:44:33.130
Nothing to know.

00:44:33.130 --> 00:44:34.055
Just relax.

00:44:56.860 --> 00:44:59.529
Let go of all your
efforts, and relax.

00:45:14.688 --> 00:45:15.666
(CHANTING) Om.

00:45:21.070 --> 00:45:29.480
Loka samasta sukhino bhuvantu.

00:45:32.560 --> 00:45:44.420
Om shanti, shanti, shanti.

00:46:00.590 --> 00:46:03.210
Gently, let's take
another deep breath in.

00:46:06.707 --> 00:46:08.680
And slowly exhale.

00:46:25.350 --> 00:46:28.892
And slowly and gradually
become aware of the body

00:46:28.892 --> 00:46:29.600
and surroundings.

00:46:35.745 --> 00:46:40.420
And whenever we feel
like it, at our own pace,

00:46:40.420 --> 00:46:42.340
we may open our eyes.

00:46:42.340 --> 00:46:43.330
Take your own time.

00:46:43.330 --> 00:46:44.398
There's no hurry.

00:46:53.960 --> 00:46:54.560
Good morning.

00:47:00.680 --> 00:47:03.464
It just took a few minutes.

00:47:03.464 --> 00:47:09.270
Yet, after all that talk,
just a few minutes of eyes

00:47:09.270 --> 00:47:11.520
closed felt so relaxing.

00:47:15.170 --> 00:47:17.000
And this is the power
of our own mind.

00:47:20.690 --> 00:47:23.950
And as we can explore
deeper and get

00:47:23.950 --> 00:47:28.500
to know more about all these
aspects of ourself, something

00:47:28.500 --> 00:47:32.490
that is so-- seems
inconsequential,

00:47:32.490 --> 00:47:33.900
can have great consequences.

00:47:36.770 --> 00:47:38.930
Something that starts
off very simple,

00:47:38.930 --> 00:47:42.380
just moving the
shoulders, can eventually

00:47:42.380 --> 00:47:44.500
have an impact on the mind.

00:47:44.500 --> 00:47:47.990
And this is the knowledge from
the Vedas, how all of this

00:47:47.990 --> 00:47:48.740
is interconnected.

00:47:52.180 --> 00:47:57.030
It's like when you catch one
leg of the chair and pull,

00:47:57.030 --> 00:48:00.240
all the other legs
come together.

00:48:00.240 --> 00:48:05.530
In that sense, all of this
knowledge, all the Vedas,

00:48:05.530 --> 00:48:07.570
it has so much to offer us.

00:48:07.570 --> 00:48:11.700
And we start from somewhere,
with some small technique

00:48:11.700 --> 00:48:14.910
somewhere, and that
opens up something

00:48:14.910 --> 00:48:18.220
that is useful not
just for ourself,

00:48:18.220 --> 00:48:25.380
but not interaction with--
it helps in so many ways.

00:48:25.380 --> 00:48:28.760
That's been my-- for
the last 20 years,

00:48:28.760 --> 00:48:30.450
I have been teaching
these techniques,

00:48:30.450 --> 00:48:34.140
talking to people across
the world, traveling.

00:48:34.140 --> 00:48:39.280
And it's been so satisfying
to see all these techniques

00:48:39.280 --> 00:48:40.645
having such an impact.

00:48:45.800 --> 00:48:50.280
So I love doing this,
and this is what I do.

00:48:50.280 --> 00:48:54.930
And I can go on and on and on,
because this is my passion.

00:48:54.930 --> 00:48:58.640
But I can see that we are almost
close to just five minutes away

00:48:58.640 --> 00:48:59.240
from the end.

00:48:59.240 --> 00:49:03.740
It's been one hour that
we have been sitting here.

00:49:03.740 --> 00:49:05.586
It doesn't feel like it.

00:49:05.586 --> 00:49:08.120
So if you have any
questions, anything to ask

00:49:08.120 --> 00:49:12.052
or anything to say,
please feel free to.

00:49:12.052 --> 00:49:14.010
AUDIENCE: So I had a
question about the comment

00:49:14.010 --> 00:49:19.090
that you made about doing
this while you're eating.

00:49:19.090 --> 00:49:21.090
And I know maybe
it's just a joke,

00:49:21.090 --> 00:49:24.450
but I read some
research on the subject,

00:49:24.450 --> 00:49:27.740
and I found that
not eating actually

00:49:27.740 --> 00:49:30.512
causes people stress, people
who are trying to lose weight.

00:49:30.512 --> 00:49:31.470
DINESH KASHIKAR: Right.

00:49:31.470 --> 00:49:33.511
AUDIENCE: And so it's
actually counterproductive,

00:49:33.511 --> 00:49:36.174
because that stress causes
them to want to eat more.

00:49:36.174 --> 00:49:37.090
DINESH KASHIKAR: More.

00:49:37.090 --> 00:49:37.475
Right.

00:49:37.475 --> 00:49:38.891
AUDIENCE: And so
that's a problem.

00:49:38.891 --> 00:49:41.816
So I was wondering if
that's just a joke,

00:49:41.816 --> 00:49:43.720
or if you have a few
words to say on--

00:49:43.720 --> 00:49:45.011
DINESH KASHIKAR: On not eating.

00:49:45.011 --> 00:49:45.929
AUDIENCE: Yes.

00:49:45.929 --> 00:49:47.720
DINESH KASHIKAR: So,
yeah, in that context,

00:49:47.720 --> 00:49:52.050
obviously I wanted to
lighten up the atmosphere,

00:49:52.050 --> 00:49:55.010
and it was not part of my talk.

00:49:55.010 --> 00:49:58.090
But usually, when I
conduct a yoga session,

00:49:58.090 --> 00:50:02.030
like some of these, it helps
to lighten up the atmosphere.

00:50:02.030 --> 00:50:03.880
That changes the
state of the mind.

00:50:03.880 --> 00:50:09.320
So yes, in that sense, it was
intended more as a bit levity

00:50:09.320 --> 00:50:13.160
rather than
something so serious.

00:50:13.160 --> 00:50:16.950
In Sanskrit, there is a saying
which says [SPEAKING SANSKRIT].

00:50:16.950 --> 00:50:20.240
It means excess of
anything is not good.

00:50:20.240 --> 00:50:24.530
So in that sense, I would
say moderation definitely

00:50:24.530 --> 00:50:30.421
is the way to go, neither going
overboard nor going underboard.

00:50:30.421 --> 00:50:33.010
Yeah, you're right.

00:50:33.010 --> 00:50:34.457
AUDIENCE: I think
I read somewhere

00:50:34.457 --> 00:50:41.970
that your breath pattern follows
the quote unquote "moon cycle."

00:50:41.970 --> 00:50:46.660
And so that's why you
breathe in from one nostril,

00:50:46.660 --> 00:50:49.380
and it switches to the
other, and it repeats.

00:50:49.380 --> 00:50:55.510
And so when you
switch, artificially,

00:50:55.510 --> 00:51:01.097
how to breathe, what's
the significance of that?

00:51:01.097 --> 00:51:03.305
DINESH KASHIKAR: I'm sure
there are many studies that

00:51:03.305 --> 00:51:08.510
are happening, but
I would say there

00:51:08.510 --> 00:51:11.570
are a lot of aspects
of own physiology

00:51:11.570 --> 00:51:13.990
that we are still exploding.

00:51:13.990 --> 00:51:16.380
We really don't know
much about ourself,

00:51:16.380 --> 00:51:23.950
and the envelope of knowledge
is increasing day by day.

00:51:23.950 --> 00:51:26.070
One thing which is a
very interesting study

00:51:26.070 --> 00:51:29.860
is how our breath
patterns keep changing,

00:51:29.860 --> 00:51:32.170
like you just mentioned.

00:51:32.170 --> 00:51:35.610
If you notice, sometimes
we feel one nostril

00:51:35.610 --> 00:51:36.990
is more active than the other.

00:51:36.990 --> 00:51:38.140
And this keeps flipping.

00:51:38.140 --> 00:51:40.970
It keeps changing.

00:51:40.970 --> 00:51:44.340
What I have experienced by
doing all these practice,

00:51:44.340 --> 00:51:48.530
especially the nadi sodhana,
the alternate nostril breathing,

00:51:48.530 --> 00:51:51.570
is it helps to calm the
mind in a certain way.

00:51:51.570 --> 00:51:53.530
Of course, all this
is anecdotal evidence.

00:51:53.530 --> 00:51:56.820
More and more people who do
this find it easier to meditate.

00:51:59.550 --> 00:52:01.490
What happens during this thing?

00:52:01.490 --> 00:52:04.645
I'm not a medical practitioner
nor a medical researcher,

00:52:04.645 --> 00:52:09.010
so I really don't know about
it, nor is it appropriate

00:52:09.010 --> 00:52:10.620
for me to comment about it.

00:52:10.620 --> 00:52:13.610
But as a yoga teacher,
I've seen this technique

00:52:13.610 --> 00:52:15.615
used very effectively
before a meditation.

00:52:15.615 --> 00:52:20.050
It helps the mind to calm
down and to be more balanced.

00:52:20.050 --> 00:52:24.780
So I would hazard a guess,
I would say that, you know,

00:52:24.780 --> 00:52:26.860
breathing in different
patterns helps

00:52:26.860 --> 00:52:30.590
to make an impact on
the state of the mind.

00:52:30.590 --> 00:52:32.910
Usually some of the
questions that I get asked

00:52:32.910 --> 00:52:37.610
is, after this, it's easy to
come and sit here and meditate

00:52:37.610 --> 00:52:39.780
when you're giving instructions.

00:52:39.780 --> 00:52:42.890
But how do I do it on my own?

00:52:42.890 --> 00:52:47.990
Usually, when I sit on my own,
my mind goes here and there.

00:52:47.990 --> 00:52:49.800
So one takeaway-- oh,
